            <scopecontent id="aspace_fa41d509d0ddad0a7b028f3fa04ef1d2">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>The 2012-A-060 accession consists of one folder containing four photographs of Simon Samoeil, curator of the Near East Collection, Yale University Library, providing a guided tour of the "Middle Eastern and Islamic Cuisine" exhibition in Sterling Memorial Library.  The exhibition ran from February 1 through April 19, 2007 in the Sterling Cloiser.</p>
               <p>The guided tour was part of the workshop "Sweet &amp; Savory: Teaching to the Senses at the Corssroads of Civilizations" that was organized by PIER (Programs in International Educational Resources) and the Council on Middle Eastern Studies at the MacMillan Center, Yale University.</p>
               <p>All four photographs were taken by Anthony Riccio, Access Services Administration, Sterling Memorial Library.</p>
            </scopecontent>
